      Things happen
   =20
 =20

The World Economic Forum in Davos,=C2=A0the place where billionaires fly in=
 on private jets to find solutions to income inequality and climate change,=
 is=C2=A0allegedly a toxic workplace.=C2=A0The foreign investors left stran=
ded in Evergrande=E2=80=99s web of Chinese debt. Philippines courts investo=
rs for =E2=80=98China-free=E2=80=99 nickel supply chain.=C2=A0A Real-Estate=
 Fund Industry Is Bleeding Billions After Starwood Capped Withdrawals. Blac=
kRock Enters Booming Market for Stock ETFs With a 100% Hedge. Citi was mone=
y launderers=E2=80=99 favourite bank, US law enforcement officials say. Boe=
ing Scoops Up Spirit AeroSystems, Its Troubled 737 Supplier. UniCredit Seek=
s Clarity From Court After ECB Orders Russia Cuts. Nomura seeks global acqu=
isitions to expand wealth management business. Wall Street Cop Finra Goes Q=
