emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;">don=E2=80=99t know man</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Shares of Chewy climbed after the influential =
retail trader known by his online moniker =E2=80=9CRoaring Kitty=E2=80=9D d=
isclosed a 6.6% stake in the online pet-products retailer.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The stock was up 20% at $32.72 in premarket tr=
ading. Shares had gained 15% year to date as of Friday=E2=80=99s market clo=
se.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Keith Gill=E2=80=99s stake was disclosed in a =
regulatory filing days after posting a photo of a dog on his account on X.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The cryptic post fueled speculation that Gill,=
 whose advocacy of GameStop in 2021 spurred massive gain in that retailer=
=E2=80=99s stock, was also throwing his support behind Chewy, which was fou=
nded by GameStop CEO Ryan Cohen.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Chewy=E2=80=99s stock spiked after Gill=E2=80=
=99s post last Thursday, jumping from the prior day=E2=80=99s close of $29.=
15 to a high of $35.95 in midday trading, only to then sink back to around =
$29 by the time the market closed.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gill=E2=80=99s filing with the Securities and =
Exchange Commission, dated June 24 and made public Monday, shows that he ow=
ns 9 million shares in Chewy. Gill checked a box on the filing noting that =
he is =E2=80=9Cnot a cat,=E2=80=9D a distinction he made to lawmakers in hi=
s 2021 congressional testimony in the GameStop saga.</p>
</blockquote>
