<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Two brothers found guilty of stealing scrap me=
tal from the Oconomowoc Area School District have been fighting for eight y=
ears to keep their jobs with the district.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Their case is now headed to the Wisconsin Supr=
eme Court.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gregory and Jeff Cota were part of the school =
district=E2=80=99s grounds crew. An investigation in 2014 found the brother=
s, a supervisor and co-worker kept more than $5,000 that was supposed to be=
 turned over to the district after they recycled scrap metal, according to =
the lawsuit.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Police investigated the case. The Cotas were i=
ssued citations for municipal theft.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Cotas agreed to pay $500 restitution to th=
e school district, and they were ultimately fired for theft in 2016.=C2=A0<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2021, the state=E2=80=99s Labor and Industr=
y Review Commission found the Oconomowoc School District violated the Wisco=
nsin Fair Employment Act=E2=80=99s prohibition against arrest record discri=
mination.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That was reversed on appeal, but it=E2=80=99s =
now before the state supreme court, so who knows. It=E2=80=99s possible tha=
t the rule is that, if you commit crimes at work, you can be fired=C2=A0<em=
>or=C2=A0</em>prosecuted, but not both.</p>
